I"â<p>One problem that can leave your system unstable is dependencies or orphaned packages leaving after you uninstall a package.</p>

<p>This problem  can be solved by installing a tool called <strong>debfoster</strong>. It tracks what you have installed and ask you to uninstall dependencies files when you uninstalled a program.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">//install
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get <span class="nb">install </span>debfoster

//help
<span class="nb">sudo </span>debfoster <span class="nt">--help</span>

//create initial keeper
<span class="nb">sudo </span>debfoster <span class="nt">-q</span>

//system to conform to keeper
<span class="nb">sudo </span>debfoster <span class="nt">-f</span>

//check orphaned/dependencies files
<span class="nb">sudo </span>debfoster</code></pre></figure>

<p>More information: <a href="http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=24403" target="_blank">using debfoster in practice</a></p>
